

## **Decentralized Exchanges (DEXs)**
    
Decentralized exchanges (DEXs) let users trade digital tokens directly with each other using smart contracts, without the need for a centralized entity.

A popular example of a DEX is an Automated Market Maker (AMM).

**Automated Market Makers (AMMs)**

AMMs use the concept of liquidity pools instead of order books.

Liquidity Pools are pre-funded pools with pairs of tokens (e.g ETH/USDC) allowing users to trade instantly! All trading activity is controlled by the poolâ€™s smart contract.

Algorithms within the smart contract determine the price of each token and adjust prices in real time based on supply and demand. This ensures that the supply of each token in a pool is always proportional to the other tokens in the pool.

**How Liquidity Pools Work?**

- Liquidity Providers add ETH and USDC into the liquidity pool
- Traders swap ETH for USDC from the liquidity pool  
	
- Liquidity Providers receive a share of the trading fees in proportion to the amount of liquidity they have supplied to the pool
